# ── Google Drive (Signals tab — shared-drive PDFs) ───────────────────────────
# Pulls PDFs from a shared-drive folder into the Signals reel AND feeds them to
# Claude as grounding for each scan. Uses the SAME OAuth as Sheets, but the
# refresh token must include the Drive scope — re-run `node mint-google-token.mjs`
# (it now requests drive.readonly) and paste the new GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN above.
#   GOOGLE_DRIVE_SIGNALS_FOLDER_ID — the folder id from its Drive URL
#                                    (drive.google.com/drive/folders/<THIS>)
#   GOOGLE_SHARED_DRIVE_ID         — only if the folder lives on a Shared Drive
#                                    (not "My Drive"); the drive's own id
#   GOOGLE_SIGNALS_MAX_DOCS        — max PDFs fed into a scan (optional; default 4)
# Leave FOLDER_ID blank to disable (the Drive lane degrades gracefully).
GOOGLE_DRIVE_SIGNALS_FOLDER_ID=0ABZbbd_Mvw9eUk9PVA
GOOGLE_SHARED_DRIVE_ID=0ABZbbd_Mvw9eUk9PVA
GOOGLE_SIGNALS_MAX_DOCS=

# ── Gmail (Signals tab — emails with your network) ───────────────────────────
# Pulls recent emails to/from your network + portfolio companies into the Signals
# reel. Uses the SAME OAuth as Sheets/Drive — re-run `node mint-google-token.mjs`
# (now requests gmail.readonly), paste the new GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN, and enable
# the Gmail API in the Google Cloud project. Then flip this on:
#   GMAIL_SIGNALS_ENABLED       — "true" to enable the Gmail lane (default off)
#   GMAIL_SIGNALS_WINDOW_DAYS   — how far back to look (optional; default 14)
#   GMAIL_SIGNALS_MAX           — max emails per load (optional; default 25)
#   GMAIL_SIGNALS_QUERY         — optional Gmail search to OVERRIDE the auto query,
#                                 e.g. subject:"Portco blogs" OR from:dell.com
#                                 (newer_than:<window> is prepended if you omit a date)
GMAIL_SIGNALS_ENABLED=true
GMAIL_SIGNALS_WINDOW_DAYS=14
GMAIL_SIGNALS_MAX=25
GMAIL_SIGNALS_QUERY=

